From d8989106287d3735c7e7fc6acb3811d62ebb666c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Uday M Bhat <uday.m.bhat@intel.com>
Date: Tue, 4 Feb 2025 13:39:43 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: Intel: sof_sdw: Add support for Fatcat board with BT offload enabled in PTL platform
Git-commit: d8989106287d3735c7e7fc6acb3811d62ebb666c
Patch-mainline: v6.14-rc4
References: jsc#PED-14430 jsc#PED-14297 jsc#PED-14024

    This change adds an entry for fatcat boards in soundwire quirk table
    and also, enables BT offload for PTL RVP.

Signed-off-by: Uday M Bhat <uday.m.bhat@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Jairaj Arava <jairaj.arava@intel.com>
Reviewed-by: Ranjani Sridharan <ranjani.sridharan@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Bard Liao <yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com>
Link: https://patch.msgid.link/20250204053943.93596-4-yung-chuan.liao@linux.intel.com
Signed-off-by: Mark Brown <broonie@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
index 683e15b459a1..203b07d4d833 100644
--- a/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
+++ b/sound/soc/intel/boards/sof_sdw.c
@@ -749,6 +749,16 @@ static const struct dmi_system_id sof_sdw_quirk_table[] = {
 		},
 		.driver_data = (void *)(SOC_SDW_PCH_DMIC),
 	},
+	{
+		.callback = sof_sdw_quirk_cb,
+		.matches = {
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_SYS_VENDOR, "Google"),
+			DMI_MATCH(DMI_PRODUCT_NAME, "Fatcat"),
+		},
+		.driver_data = (void *)(SOC_SDW_PCH_DMIC |
+					SOF_BT_OFFLOAD_SSP(2) |
+					SOF_SSP_BT_OFFLOAD_PRESENT),
+	},
 	{}
 };
 
